        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 7:56AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 755 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Pontotoc, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Saba, Regency, Harkeyville, Richland Springs, Locker, Cherokee,
Chappel, Sloan, Algerita, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
